mpted, nor the last, but last night I was grouped with a human druid named Hopebringer Elisian in Highhold, and he asked me to help him re-roll.  He said he would pay me a lot of money and give me his gear because he would not need it with his new character.  I agreed, so he said we would go to the Bazaar so he could give me his stuff to hold while he created a new character.  I wondered why we had to go all the way to the bazaar, and he said he would help me sell my equipment that his would replace, and that was the best place to do it.  Sounded too good to be true, but I went along with it.  After talking for about half an hour, we finally went to the Bazaar, and he told me to put all my stuff in bags so I could bank it and take his stuff and wear it.  I did that, getting more suspicious by the moment.  He then told me to put my stuff in the trade window and he would hold it for me while I took his stuff because I did not have enough spots open.  That was the moment I knew he was definitly trying to scam me.  I said forget it and walked away.  I didn't even bother acusing him because I new it would be a waste of time.  After I zoned into the Nexxus, someone sent me a tell saying Hopebringer was shouting in the Bazaar that I stole from him.  I sent him a tell saying I was petitioning a GM and we could get this all straightened out.  He logged off.  <br>
<br>
Now, I will probably never see the name Hopebringer again, unless he is a very stupid person, but I am going to follow through with this GM investigation.  By looking at the conversation him and I had it will be obvious he was trying to steal.  My word to everyone is to keep an eye out.  He will probably return under a different name, but once evil, always evil.  And remember, if it sounds too good to be true, it IS!!!<br>
<br>
Kuue Soulslinger<br>
Proud member of the Clan of Brothers<br>
33rd circle druid of Tunare<br>
<br>
