<br>
ran into him yesterday in everfrost.  he practically tried to get me killed by mammoths.  then again, i didn't have to play the gullible good samaritan, and i'm fully aware that i brought it on myself by doing so.<br>
<br>
this guy runs up to me, invites me to group without speaking a word.  i can see he's low on health, and being a bard i figure i'll group and heal/mana him up, then take off.  <br>
<br>
he says &quot;oom&quot; and sits down.  i sit to load clarity, as i don't have it loaded unless grouping (which happens rarely).  basically, he'd already aggroed a mammoth and it finally caught him up and gored the crap out of me due to bard aggro i guess.  regular mammoths are red to me, by the way.<br>
<br>
so now we're both low on health, and i'm running around trying to keep this mammoth occupied and off his hands while (i'm assuming, yes..i did assume too much)  he meds for the killing shot.  he stands up, says he dotted it, then disappears.<br>
<br>
basically, this was more than i'd signed on for.  by this time, every other mammoth in the zone is after my blood (this crap was pulled at a major mammoth intersection).  so i took off for the guards, and after reaching them said &quot;sorry, gotta run.&quot;   /disband<br>
<br>
did a /who on him right then &amp; there and he was already in highpass, probably just beginning to run whatever scam on you he was trying to pull.<br>
<br>
by the way, another person was grouped up with us at the time.  an enchantress who was nowhere in sight, but had two bubbles of health left when i joined.  i'm assuming (again) that she had already suffered from his insane behaviour and had run off in search of the guards.  as soon as she reached them, she disbanded with a similar excuse and logged.  it would be interesting to hear what she has to say.  her name was Saladdilla, if i remember correctly.   <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ulunathreee.showPublicProfile?language=EN>lunathreee</A> at: 8/11/02 9:17:45 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uralkorravenblood.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ralkor Ravenblood</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 12<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/12/02 5:33:10 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: my brief experience with this person</span><hr size=1> I met Hopebringer yesterday and he is now on my ignore list. I met him in Solusek's Eye, and not having read this post, I trusted him. <br>
<br>
I grouped with him for a while and while he surely was not a roleplayer or someone I would go on vacation with, I had met worse (hi Maladil). Things went slow with the goblins, so he proposed to port to Steamfont and kill the minotaur Meldreth for some Hero Bracers. He said we two could do it (low 30s druid, 27 rogue.. yeah I know now), and since I did not know anything about Meldreth and that he would easily wipe us a few minutes later, I agreed. <br>
<br>
No problem so far, but when I returned to get my corpse, Hopebringer, instead of sowing me or helping otherwise, had invited a local gnome for language lessons.. nothing more enjoyable than groupchat-spam on a corpse run. I got my corpse without his help, and when he called me 'dude' a few minutes later, he had earned his place on my ignore-list.<br>
<br>
